cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the task of fine-grained vehicle classification using deep learning architectures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses various aspects of CNN training, such as data augmentation and training from scratch vs. fine-tuning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning architectures for classification also falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper uses the Stanford Cars-196 dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and the task of vehicle search, re-identification, tracking, and traffic analysis, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
